<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB7EF74FF42FB33FDF8FAB5" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FB33FA85FB51" blockId="31.[151,1436,1086,1293]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FB33FEE7FB18" bold="true" box="[199,338,1158,1184]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first record of the species after its original description. Even if a 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FFB7EF74FB20FB32FAB9FB19" box="[1189,1292,1159,1185]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">lectotype</typeStatus>
are yet to be designed, specimens have been safely identified as they present a conspicuous and singular diagonal white stripe from the eye towards the inferior border of the lateral lobes of pronotum, besides the entirely white gena.
</paragraph>
